  "summary": "Moderate: c-ares security update",
  "details": "The c-ares C library defines asynchronous DNS (Domain Name System) requests and provides name resolving API.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* c-ares: Heap buffer over read in ares_parse_soa_reply (CVE-2020-22217)\n* c-ares: Buffer Underwrite in ares_inet_net_pton() (CVE-2023-31130)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
